Hi, Eugene,

it seems I found how this KASSERT can be triggered.
The ip6_output function has this part of code:

routefound:
if (rt && !IN6_IS_ADDR_MULTICAST(&ip6->ip6_dst)) {
        if (opt && opt->ip6po_nextroute.ro_rt) {
                /*
                 * The nexthop is explicitly specified by the
                 * application.  We assume the next hop is an IPv6
                 * address.
                 */
                dst = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)opt->ip6po_nexthop;
        }
        else if ((rt->rt_flags & RTF_GATEWAY))
                dst = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)rt->rt_gateway;
}

There a dst pointer can be changed to the rt->rt_gateway, that in your
case has non IPv6 address. Then, the nd6_output_lle() does lla_lookup()
for this address and it triggers KASSERT when INVARIANTS is enabled.
Not sure that this is a correct fix, but I think, it should work like
when INVARIANTS is disabled. You can try attached patch.

-- 
WBR, Andrey V. Elsukov
